<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10040f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10040f">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10040f"> 40(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> reserved sin</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Doing the Devil&apos;s Work <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Deliberate Perjury</b> <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> It is well-known that perjury is a <mark>reserved sin</mark>. <small> <a name="CT12apr24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CT12apr24"><cite title="source">Connacht Tribune</cite></a> (12 April 1924) 5/2-3</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Reserved sin. A term used in the Catholic church for sins whose absolution is not within the power of every confessor, but is reserved to himself by the superior of the confessor, or only specially granted to some other confessor by that superior.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c01017h" href="c01all.htm#c01017h">VI.C.01:017(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
